release_note: Minor Fixes and Improvements We are constantly working on updates to provide the best self care and gratitude experience. Thank you for using Gratitude to brighten your days.
New: Prompted Reflections. Now it s easier to find inspiration when you need it. General improvements Thank you for using Gratefully
Visual and stability improvements Thank you for using Gratefully!
Routine improvements Ocean Theme Improvements: Favourite affirmation text colour Breath exercises start button didn t show before Thank you for finding happiness in your life with Gratefully

Welcome to Gratefully v4! The biggest update to the app ever! Now you can add stickers to your new moments New Explore section now it s so easy to find all the features of the app and navigate to them with a simple tap. Your data safe. Automatic backup to your iCloud account. New weekly view on the agenda for those users who prefer the old calendar is still available. Statistics redesigned. Now you can find Gratitude points on the last tab of the app with the statistics section. It helps you to be rewarded in your steps to happiness. New Routine feature designed to help you be consistent on your self care and gratitude journey. Redesigned sections: Quotes Affirmations and Resolutions. If you have previous quotes you won t lose them they will still appear. But now you can add new quotes and easily manage them. It you have previous resolutions please ada them again. Sorry for the inconvenience but l think the redesign is much better. Minor improvements Fixed a problem with Widgets Fixed a onboarding issue As you can see there are a lot of new features and I hope you enjoy them as much as I enjoyed developing them. Thanks for using Gratefully!

In the last version we added Resolutions so that you have on hand the goals you want to achieve this year. Writing down resolutions for the year can be beneficial because it allows you to set concrete and defined goals and objectives for the coming year. By writing resolutions you can: 1. Set priorities: By writing down your resolutions you can think carefully about what is most important to you and how you want to focus your time and energy during the coming year. 2. Create an action plan: By having concrete and defined goals you can create an action plan to achieve your resolutions and break them down into more manageable steps. 3. Motivate yourself to keep going: By having your resolutions written down you can use them as a motivational tool to keep going and not get sidetracked from your goals. 4. Review your progress: By writing down your resolutions you can review them regularly to see how you are progressing and make adjustments to your action plan if necessary. 5. Improve your life: By setting goals and working towards them you can improve your life in a number of ways whether personally professionally or financially. Writing resolutions for the year can be beneficial because it allows you to set concrete and defined goals and objectives create a plan of action motivate yourself to keep going review your progress and improve your life.
